>> servings: 4
>> source: https://www.bonappetit.com/recipe/basic-bulgogi
>> time required: 70 minutes

Combine grated @pear{1/4}, grated @garlic{1%clove}, @soy sauce{2%tbsp}, @gochugaru{1%tbsp}, @gochujang{1%tbsp}, grated @ginger{1%tbsp}, @light brown sugar{1%tbsp}, and @sesame oil{1%tbsp} in a #large resealable plastic bag{} or #medium bowl{}. Using a #sharp knife{}, slice @strip steak{1%lb} into very thin strips. Add to marinade, seal bag, and squish everything around until the meat is coated. Let's sit at room temperature for ~{30%minutes}, or chill up to ~{8%hours}.

Heat @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in a #large skillet{} over medium high until oil is shimmering. Remove Half of the meat from the marinade, letting the excess drip back into the bag. Season lightly with @salt and cook in a single layer without moving until lightly browned, about ~{1%minute}. Toss the meat and continue to cook, tossing occasionally, until cooked through and crisp at edges, about ~{4%minutes}. Transfer to a plate. Repeat with remaining 1 tbsp, vegetable oil, remaining meat, and more salt.

Serve topped with @scallions, @sesame seeds{}, and @plum sauce{}.
